<dl id="n14068d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14068d">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14068d"> 68(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> &amp; Goethe, pity / for his little Deutsch</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>Goethe</mark>&apos;s vision, indeed, expressed as much when he said: &ldquo;Do not imagine that I am indifferent to the great ideas of Freedom, People, Fatherland. No, indeed! These ideas are within us; they are part of our being and none should dare cast them aside. Germany, too, has a warm corner in my heart; many a time have I felt bitter pain when thinking of <mark>the German people</mark>, who are so worthy of respect, individually, yet <mark>so pitiful</mark> when viewed as a whole. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> &rdquo; <small> Ernst Boldt, <a name="BFLS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BFLS"><cite title="source">From Luther to Steiner</cite></a>, (1921) 28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
